{"session_id":"svc-1778112908334281126","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-07T00:15:08.543976042Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","sticky":{"key_present":true,"assignment":"not_applicable"},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-d3aca2b7-20260507T001505-38837f5f","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260507T001505-38837f5f/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260507T001505-38837f5f/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260507T001505-38837f5f/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260507T001505-38837f5f/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260507T001505-38837f5f/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-d3aca2b7\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003etest: cover task execution cleanup and resource exhaustion end-to-end\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;The cleanup/resource contract needs an end-to-end regression harness, not only isolated unit tests. The May 6 failure crossed command, git worktree, tracker claim, resource classification, and operator-output boundaries: a unit-only suite could still miss the exact behavior where ddx work claims the next bead after ENOSPC.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:686-718 owns real git worktree setup/cleanup, while cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:437-530 owns queue drain loop state; existing tests cover many individual branches but not the full resource-exhausted incident path.\u0026#xA;- cli/cmd/try.go:306-342 and cli/cmd/work.go:101 route command contexts into workers, but there is no command-level e2e test proving cleanup/resource failures produce correct operator output and tracker state.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/run_state_test.go:95-145 tests orphan recovery shapes, but not full DDx temp root cleanup plus registered worktree pruning plus claim safety.\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md:449-498 requires cleanup to be inline, loop-level, background, observable, and loop-fatal on resource exhaustion.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Add end-to-end tests that use a temp project, temp DDX_EXEC_WT_DIR, real git worktree commands where feasible, and injectable resource-check failures where filling a filesystem would be unsafe.\u0026#xA;- Verify tracker state after failure: no extra bead claimed, failed bead open/re-claimable, no retry-after cooldown for host resource exhaustion.\u0026#xA;- Verify cleanup state after failure: stale unregistered dirs and stale registered worktrees are removed; active/preserved evidence survives.\u0026#xA;- Verify operator output and loop events contain cleanup summary and resource_exhausted stop reason.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not create a real ENOSPC by filling /tmp or exhausting inodes in CI.\u0026#xA;- Do not require live harness/model/provider calls.\u0026#xA;- Do not test unrelated production-reachability bead content.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestWorkResourceExhaustionEndToEnd_StopsBeforeNextClaim runs ddx work against two ready beads with injected resource_exhausted setup failure and verifies only the first bead is touched.\u0026#xA;2. TestWorkCleanupEndToEnd_PrunesStaleRegisteredAndUnregisteredWorktrees creates real stale DDx worktrees/dirs under a temp DDX_EXEC_WT_DIR and verifies ddx work or ddx cleanup prunes them safely.\u0026#xA;3. TestTryResourceExhaustionEndToEnd_Reclaimable verifies ddx try on a target bead fails with resource_exhausted, exits non-zero, and leaves the bead open/unclaimed without execute-loop-retry-after.\u0026#xA;4. TestCleanupEndToEnd_PreservesPublishedEvidence verifies complete .ddx/executions and .ddx/runs bundles plus refs/ddx/iterations/* are not removed.\u0026#xA;5. TestBackgroundCleanupEndToEnd_UsesLockAndJitter verifies periodic cleanup can be driven deterministically with fake time and does not run concurrent destructive passes.\u0026#xA;6. The e2e tests use temp directories and injectable fakes rather than consuming real disk/inodes.\u0026#xA;7. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/... ./internal/agent/... -run \u0026#34;TestWorkResourceExhaustionEndToEnd|TestWorkCleanupEndToEnd|TestTryResourceExhaustionEndToEnd|TestCleanupEndToEnd|TestBackgroundCleanupEndToEnd\u0026#34; -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:test, area:agent, area:cli, kind:test, reliability, spec:FEAT-010, spec:SD-025, cleanup, resource-exhaustion, e2e\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-f3dfde0d\" spec-id=\"FEAT-010\" base-rev=\"c0daa5dc8e5f6caebad5bf8807bfca58bf60e403\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260507T001505-38837f5f\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"FEAT-010\" path=\"docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md\"\u003eFeature: Task Execution\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260507T001505-38837f5f","base_rev":"c0daa5dc8e5f6caebad5bf8807bfca58bf60e403","bead_id":"ddx-d3aca2b7","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260507T001505-38837f5f","correlation_id":"ddx-d3aca2b7:20260507T001505-38837f5f","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260507T001505-38837f5f/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"904e146275fdf3c6a88128163ae73a1c7bf95ff2ffc71ad5d2366e9f27e666d5","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-2633f2f0","worker_id":""}}}
